real life life hack: use the flower beauty bomb blush as a liquid lip!

I bought a color wanting to try it and it looked AWFUL as blush and I was mad it was such a waste, so I tried it on my lips just to see if I could make it work somehow and oh my god.

not only is the shade I have a gorgeous lip color but it's the BEST liquid lip formula I have ever tried. Not drying at all and does not move. It's so so nice, 10/10 recommend to all my fellow makeup wearers who can't stand lipstick or liquid lips usually.

snippet.textDisplay: tati, Tati...  TATI...!!!  I am a new subscriber...  I have binge-watched so many of your videos over the past month and finally rang the bell today!!  I just wanted to let you know to be very VERY careful with that Neutrogena Ultra Sheer Sunscreen Spray...  it is full of chemical sunscreens that are KNOWN HORMONE/ENDOCRINE DISRUPTORS...  I know you do A LOT of research on what you use and because you take such great care and concern with what goes INTO your body and what's in the products you produce, I thought you would want to know.  These chemicals get into your bloodstream rather quickly, the skin IS the largest organ after all, and can do some really bad things...  I am a fellow endo-girl and these chemicals can exacerbate the pain and discomfort of endometriosis because of the way they interact with your body's hormones.  I don't know if there's a similar looking and feeling product out there that you could to duplicate the effect you get when using that sunscreen spray on the manner you do, but that might be a good challenge and video idea for you.  I just don't want you to suffer with endo any more than you do as I know the same suffering firsthand...  just looking out for you.  I love your channel, another YouTube creator recommended your channel and I am so So SO happy she did!!! 😊💕
